{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbd60c6be-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s5849"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5849"},"text":"§ 5849.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Other officers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd60c6bf-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s5849/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Executive Director","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Commission shall appoint an Executive Director for Operations, who shall serve at the pleasure of and be removable by the Commission.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd60c6c0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s5849/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Functions of Executive Director","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Executive Director shall perform such functions as the Commission may direct, except that the Executive Director shall not limit the authority of the director of any component organization provided in this chapter to communicate with or report directly to the Commission when such director of a component organization deems it necessary to carry out his responsibilities. Notwithstanding the preceding sentence, each such director shall keep the Executive Director fully and currently informed concerning the content of all such direct communications with the Commission.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd60c6c1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s5849/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Equal employment opportunity report","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Executive Director shall report to the Commission at semi-annual public meetings on the problems, progress, and status of the Commission’s equal employment opportunity efforts.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd60c6c2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s5849/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Annual status report","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Executive Director shall prepare and forward to the Commission an annual report (for the fiscal year 1978 and each succeeding fiscal year) on the status of the Commission’s programs concerning domestic safeguards matters including an assessment of the effectiveness and adequacy of safeguards at facilities and activities licensed by the Commission. The Commission shall forward to the Congress a report under this section prior to ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-02-01"},"text":"February 1, 1979","children":[],"tail":", as a separate document, and prior to February 1 of each succeeding year as a separate chapter of the Commission’s annual report (required under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s5877/c"},"text":"section 5877(c) of this title","children":[],"tail":") following the fiscal year to which such report applies."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbd60c6c3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s5849/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Additional officers","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"There shall be in the Commission not more than five additional officers appointed by the Commission. The positions of such officers shall be considered career positions and be subject to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2201/d"},"text":"section 2201(d) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbd60c6c4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/438/tII/s209"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–438, title II, § 209","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-10-11"},"text":"Oct. 11, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1248"},"text":"88 Stat. 1248","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/601"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–601","children":[],"tail":", §§ 4, 6, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-06"},"text":"Nov. 6, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/2949"},"text":"92 Stat. 2949","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbd60c6c5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbd60c6c6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbd60c6c7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in subsec. (b), was in the original “this Act”, meaning ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/438"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–438","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-10-11"},"text":"Oct. 11, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1233"},"text":"88 Stat. 1233","children":[],"tail":", known as the Energy Reorganization Act of 1974, which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s5801"},"text":"section 5801 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbd60c6c8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1978—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/601/s4/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–601, § 4(a)","children":[],"tail":", inserted provision requiring component organization directors to keep the Executive Director informed as to communications with the Commission."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/601/s4/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–601, § 4(b)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (c). Former subsec. (c) redesignated (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/601/s6"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–601, § 6","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (d)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/601/s4/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–601, § 4(b)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated former subsec. (c) as (e)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbd60c6c9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idbd60c6ca-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Termination of Reporting Requirements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For termination, effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-05-15"},"text":"May 15, 2000","children":[],"tail":", of provisions in subsec. (d) of this section relating to forwarding of annual report to Congress, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/66/s3003"},"text":"section 3003 of Pub. L. 104–66","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t31/s1113"},"text":"section 1113 of Title 31","children":[],"tail":", Money and Finance, and the 10th item on page 186 of House Document No. 103–7."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"idbd630fbb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"idbd630fbc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For transfer of certain functions from Nuclear Regulatory Commission to Chairman thereof, see Reorg. Plan No. 1 of 1980, 45 F.R. 40561, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/3585"},"text":"94 Stat. 3585","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s5841"},"text":"section 5841 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
